        {
          "username": "Yearim Leslie Yi",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "101183318121375710032",
          "user_review_count": 337,
          "user_photo_count": 666,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUkkzglwIkXzP6TDYOa-je8mC5vpMb9VhtK4ffhqav545JIalJuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "While the exterior of the building looks a bit outdated and the surrounding roads can be hectic with double-parked ambulances, my experience at NYPH LM was overall positive.\n\nI visited the ER and the Labor & Delivery department, and both experiences were made great by the attentive and accommodating staff. The ER was well-equipped, and they were thorough in testing to rule out potential issues.\n\nThe Labor & Delivery department is currently undergoing renovations to add more private rooms. I was fortunate enough to have a private room in May 2025 (obviously not one of the renovated ones). Despite the facilities being a bit worn, I had no major complaints thanks to the excellent staff.\nThe food could be improved, but I think that\u2019s to be expected at a hospital.\n\nTL;DR: The facilities are a bit dated, but the staff is amazing.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VKend0SUtXdlpfTmVREAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x92da9e7eb069aebf!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEJzwtIKWvZ_NeQ%7C%7C?hl=en",
