        {
          "username": "Laura Birenbaum",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "108403506575628340580",
          "user_review_count": 17,
          "user_photo_count": 4,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXa8iS0n_BBad70MtW4PFBOKnqOf1PEg_MjZZm3HMQCVco_xkgd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "The best ER I have ever been to! This hospital is filled with kind and caring professionals.  Despite how intensive the job is caring for so many sick people, NYP made me feel like they had a royal flush of compassionate staff members from the guy who brought me a blanket to the suite of kind nurses and doctors who looked after me. Originally I told my husband to drop me off and go home, but once I got inside, I said he should join me because it\u2019s so nice inside!  I had zero wait to be seen, which was incredibly lucky, and the ER felt calm, organized, and comfortable!  Their hospital beds are like next level memory foam.  Best of all, they treated me to take away my acute symptoms and they ran tests to confirm that I wasn\u2019t dying.  Btw, they have parking garages across the street and around the corner.  The parking cost $18 for 4 hours!!!   Were we in the Little Ohio part of NYC that I didn\u2019t know about?  So cheap!!   Overall, high praise for NYP-LM.  Thank you guys!!!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xFNWRYQkRVMDVxU25sVE5tNTZTR2RWWHpGWmRuYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x92da9e7eb069aebf!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlE5dXBDU05qSnlTNm56SGdVXzFZdnc%7C%7C?hl=en",
