        {
          "username": "Rodney Robertson",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "114845842585743268253",
          "user_review_count": 4,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTyspmTp-2VE0FVEj-eRs4CeWfQoBQuy-435757FSMpC-CLg9h=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Horrible experience ,  had an allergic reaction & was throwing up all the way to the ER.  Get to the ER & a nurse came semi fast & asked me the usual questions.  I told them I was dehydrated because I\u2019ve been throwing up, no water or just was given.  I fall asleep & wake up to the doctor asking me what was wrong which led to his decision to discharge me & just give me a Benadryl.   He leaves & another female comes to give me the Benadryl. I fall asleep for 10 mins.  Then later another female came asking for my insurance info which i provided I felt super dizzy at the time & the lady told me to relax & sit for another 15 mins til im not dizzy.  I asked her for something to drink & nobody ever came.  I then wake up 5 mins later to the female who gave me the Benadryl yelling at me to leave the hospital like I was crazy or wanted to stay when I was just told to relax for 15 mins til IM not longer dizzy.  At that point I felt extremely disrespected & disregarded.   I had to get up & physically get a drink for myself.  I was told to go to the emergency room for hydration & stomach issues from the reaction yet  the doctor just gave me a Benadryl which I could of easily taken at home\u2026\n\nIf you need to go to the ER , I suggest ask the ambulance to take you somewhere else.  Especially for your loved ones.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tNNVRHRTNhVkF0TlVsWlYzbHhhVVpUZFZWWllYYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x92da9e7eb069aebf!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkM5TGE3aVAtNUlZV3lxaUZTdVVZYXc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "5 months ago",
